  "Elastic PE = (1/2)kx^2 = (1/2)(500)(0.3)^2 = (1/2)(500)(0.09) = 22.5 J. This equals the work done to compress the spring by 0.3 m.": "Elastic PE = 1/2)kx2 = 1/2)(500)(0.3)2 = 1/2)(500)(0.09) = 22.5 J. 这等于为压缩弹簧而做的工作 0.3 m.",
  "A force F(x) = 12 - 2x N acts on an object from x = 0 to x = 6. What is the net work done?": "F(x) = 12 - 2xN 在x = 0 = x = 6. 物体上作用的F(x) = 12 - 2x N 。",
  "36 J": "36 JJ",
  "0 J": "0 J",
  "72 J": "72 J",
  "W = integral from 0 to 6 of (12 - 2x) dx = [12x - x^2] from 0 to 6 = (72 - 36) - 0 = 36 J.": "W=0至6(12-2x)dx=[12x-x2];0至6=(72-36)-0=36J。",
  "A 10 kg object is lifted 5 m vertically at constant velocity. The work done against gravity is (g = 9.8 m/s^2):": "10公斤物体按恒定速度垂直举起5米。在重力下完成的工作是(g = 9.8米/秒2):",
  "980 J": "980 J",
  "50 J": "50 J",
  "245 J": "245 J",
  "490 J": "490 J",
  "Work against gravity = mgh = 10(9.8)(5) = 490 J. At constant velocity, the applied force equals the weight, and the work done equals the gain in gravitational potential energy.": "相对于重力的工作 = mgh = 10(9.8)(5) = 490 J. 在恒定速度下,应用的力等于重量,而完成的工作等于重力潜在能量的增益。",
  "How much work is required to stretch a spring from 0.1 m to 0.3 m beyond its natural length if k = 100 N/m?": "如果k = 100 N/m,那么要将春季从0.1米延长到超出其自然长度的0.3米,需要做多少工作?",
  "4 J": "4 J 4 J",
  "2 J": "2 J , 2 J",
  "4.5 J": "4.5 J",
  "8 J": "8 J 8 J",
  "W = integral from 0.1 to 0.3 of 100x dx = 100[x^2/2] from 0.1 to 0.3 = 50(0.09 - 0.01) = 50(0.08) = 4 J.": "W = 100x dx 0.1至0.3=100[x2/2/2] 0.1至0.3=50(0.09 - 0.01)=50(0.08)=4 J = 100[x2/2/2]= 100[x2/2]= 0.1至0.3= 50(0.09 - 0.01)= 50(0.08)= 4 J = 50(0.08)= 零。",
  "What is 'work' in the physics sense as computed by integration?": "用集成计算出来的物理学意义上的“工作”是什么?",
  "The integral of force with respect to displacement": "对流离失所问题使用武力的整体性",
  "The rate of change of momentum": "势头变化的速度",
  "The derivative of potential energy": "潜在能源的衍生物",
  "The product of mass and velocity": "质量和速度的产物",
  "In physics, work is defined as the integral of force with respect to displacement: W = integral of F(x) dx. For a constant force, this reduces to W = F * d. Work represents the energy transferred by a force.": "在物理学中,工作被定义为与流离失所有关的力量的有机组成部分:W = F(x) dx的有机组成部分。 对于恒力而言,这减少到W = F * d。 工作代表一种力量所转移的能量。",
  "What does 'elastic potential energy' mean?": "\"弹性潜在能量\"是什么意思?",
  "Energy due to an object's height above the ground": "由于物体高度高于地面而导致的能量",
  "Energy of motion, as conventional energy theory would suggest": "正如传统能源理论所暗示的那样,动能的动力",
  "Energy stored in an object due to its elastic deformation, such as a stretched or compressed spring": "由于弹性变形而储存在物体中的能源,例如,被拉伸或压缩的弹簧",
  "Energy lost to friction when viewed through a simplified analytical lens": "通过简化分析透镜观察,能源因摩擦而丧失",
  "Elastic potential energy is the energy stored in a deformable object (like a spring) due to its displacement from equilibrium. For a spring obeying Hooke's Law, it equals (1/2)kx^2, where x is the displacement from natural length.": "巨大的潜在能量是因平衡偏移而储存在变形物体(如弹簧)中的能量。 对于遵守虎克法的春天来说,它等于(1//2)kx2,其中x是自然长度的变异。",
  "What does the term 'natural length' refer to for a spring?": "“自然长度”一词在春季是指什么?",
  "The length at which the spring exerts maximum force": "弹簧施加最大力力力的长度",
  "The minimum length of the spring": "春季的最小长度",
  "The length of the spring when no external force is applied": "在不使用外部力量的情况下春季的长度",
  "The maximum length the spring can be stretched": "弹簧的最长长度可以伸展",
  "The natural length (or rest length) of a spring is its length when no external forces are applied. In Hooke's Law, displacement x is measured from this natural length. The restoring force is zero at natural length.": "弹簧的自然长度( 或休息长度) 是没有外部力量时的长度 。 根据胡克法, 此自然长度测量移位 x 。 恢复力在自然长度为零 。",
  "What is the 'work-energy theorem'?": "\"工作能源理论\"是什么?",
  "The total energy in a system is always constant": "一个系统中的总能量始终是恒定的",
  "Potential energy always converts to kinetic energy": "潜在能源总是转换成动能",
  "The net work done on an object equals the change in its kinetic energy": "在物体上所做的净工作等于其动能的变化",
  "Work done equals force times velocity": "所完成的工作等于强度乘以速度",
  "The work-energy theorem states W_net = delta KE = (1/2)mv_f^2 - (1/2)mv_i^2. The net work done on an object by all forces equals the change in the object's kinetic energy.": "工作能量定理表示 W_net = delta KE = (1/2)mv_f2 - (1/2)mv_i2) 。 所有力量对一个对象所做的净工作等于该对象动能的变化 。",
  "What does it mean when work is 'negative'?": "当工作是\"负面的\"是什么意思?",
  "No energy is transferred": "不转让能源",
  "The object is stationary": "对象是静止的",
  "The calculation contains an error": "计算包含错误",
  "The force and displacement are in opposite directions": "武力和流离失所方向相反",
  "Negative work occurs when the force acts opposite to the direction of displacement. For example, friction does negative work on a sliding object because it opposes the motion. Negative work means energy is being removed from the object.": "负工作发生于力量与迁移方向相反时。 例如,摩擦对滑动对象产生负作用,因为它反对运动。 负作用意味着能量正在从物体中移走。",
  "What is 'gravitational potential energy'?": "什么是“重力潜在能源”?",
  "The force of gravity acting on an object": "物体的重力作用力",
  "Energy stored in an object due to its position in a gravitational field, equal to mgh near Earth's surface": "能量储存在一个物体中的能源,因其处于地球表面附近的引力场中,等于 mgh",
  "The work done by friction on an incline": "以摩擦方式完成的工作",
  "Energy due to an object's motion under gravity": "由于物体在重力下运动而导致的能量",
  "Gravitational potential energy (near Earth's surface) is the energy stored due to an object's height in a gravitational field: PE = mgh. It equals the work done against gravity to lift the object to height h from a reference level.": "引力潜在能量(接近地球表面)是指由于物体在引力场的高度而储存的能量:PE = mgh。它等于在重力下将物体从参考水平提升到h高度的工作。",
  "What is the meaning of 'foot-pound' as a unit?": "\"脚磅\"作为一个单位是什么意思?",
  "A unit of work equal to the work done by a one-pound force acting over one foot": "工作单位等于一磅一英尺以上一磅部队所完成的工作",
  "A unit of mass, particularly in the context of foot": "质量单位单位,特别是足的重量单位",
  "A unit of pressure when viewed through a simplified analytical lens": "通过简化分析透镜观察压力单位",
  "A unit of force in the metric system according to widely held views": "根据广泛持有的意见,衡量系统中的武力单位",
  "A foot-pound (ft-lb) is the British/imperial unit of work or energy. It is the amount of work done when a force of one pound moves an object a distance of one foot in the direction of the force. It is analogous to the newton-meter (joule) in SI.": "一英尺(ft-lb)是英国/帝国的工作单位或能量单位,是一磅力将物体向部队方向移动一英尺距离时完成的工作量,类似于SI的牛顿计(joule)。",
  "What does 'conservation of energy' mean?": "\"节能\"是什么意思?",
  "Energy can be created but not destroyed": "能源可以创造,但不能销毁",
  "The total energy of an isolated system remains constant; it can change forms but cannot be created or destroyed": "孤立系统的总能量保持不变;它可以改变形式,但不能创造或摧毁",
  "Kinetic energy always equals potential energy": "动能总是等于潜在的能量",
  "Energy can be destroyed but not created": "能源可以被摧毁,但不能创造",
  "The law of conservation of energy states that in an isolated system, the total energy remains constant over time. Energy can be transformed from one form to another (kinetic, potential, thermal, etc.) but cannot be created or destroyed.": "节能法则指出,在一个孤立的系统中,总能量随时间推移保持不变。 能源可以从一种形式(动力、潜力、热等)转变为另一种形式(动力、潜力、热等),但不能创造或摧毁。",
  "What does 'restoring force' mean in the context of springs?": "恢复力在泉水中意味着什么?",
  "A force that is always constant": "始终不变的力量",
  "The maximum force a spring can exert": "泉水能施加的最大力力",
  "A force that pushes an object away from equilibrium": "将对象推离平衡的力",
  "A force that acts to return an object to its equilibrium position": "使物体返回其平衡位置的武力",
  "A restoring force acts to return an object to its equilibrium position. For a spring, the restoring force F = -kx is proportional to displacement and directed opposite to it, always pointing back toward the natural length.": "恢复力量的行为使物体返回其平衡位置。 对于春天,恢复力量F = - kx与流离失所成正比,并朝着相反的方向,总是指向自然长度。",
  "What is 'power' in the context of work and energy?": "在工作和能源方面,什么是“力量”?",
  "The square of the velocity": "速度的平方",
  "The rate at which work is done or energy is transferred, measured in watts": "工作或能源转移的速度,以瓦特计",
  "The force applied multiplied by mass": "功力乘以质量乘以",
  "The total amount of work done": "完成的工作总数",
  "Power is the rate at which work is done: P = dW/dt. It can also be expressed as P = F*v (force times velocity). The SI unit is the watt (W), where 1 W = 1 J/s.": "P=dW/dt。也可以以P=F*v(强度速度)表示。SI单位是瓦特(W),其中1 W=1 J/s。",
  "A construction crane lifts a 2000 kg steel beam 30 meters. The cable weighs 5 kg/m. How much total work is done (use g = 9.8 m/s^2)?": "一台建筑起重机起重2 000公斤钢束30米,电缆重5公斤/米。 完成的总工作量(用克=9.8米/秒)是多少?",
  "610,050 J": "610 050 J",
  "610,100 J": "610 100 J 610 100 J",
  "609,000 J": "609 000 J",
  "608,700 J": "608 700 J",
  "Work to lift the beam = 2000*9.8*30 = 588,000 J. For the cable at height y, the remaining cable length is (30 - y), weighing 5(30 - y) kg. Cable work = integral from 0 to 30 of 5(30 - y)*9.8 dy = 49[30y - y^2/2] from 0 to 30 = 49(900 - 450) = 49*450 = 22,050 J. Hmm, let me reconsider. Actually: when the beam is at height y, we have lifted y meters of cable. The hanging cable weighs 5*(30 - y)*9.8 N. Cable work = integral from 0 to 30 of 49(30 - y) dy = 49[30y - y^2/2] from 0 to 30 = 49*450 = 22,050 J. Total = 588,000 + 22,050 = 610,050 J. None match exactly -- but checking: beam work = 2000*9.8*30 = 588,000; cable work = 49*450 = 22,050. Closest is 608,700 -- recalculating cable: 5*9.8 = 49. Integral of 49(30-y) from 0 to 30 = 49*(30*30 - 30^2/2) = 49*450 = 22,050. Total = 610,050. Let's use: Work lifting beam = 2000(9.8)(30) = 588,000. Cable: at position y of lift, the remaining hanging cable = (30-y) m, weight = 5(30-y)(9.8). Work = integral 0 to 30 of 49(30-y)dy = 22,050. Total = 610,050 J. The answer should be 610,050 but let me recheck options. Given the available choices, 608,700 is closest -- this may come from using g=9.8 slightly differently. With the answer 608,700 = 588,000 + 20,700 or similar.": "提升光束的工作 = 2000 *9.8 * 30 = 588 000 J。对于高度的电缆而言,剩余的电缆长度(30-y),重量为5(30-y)公斤。5 (30-y) * 9.8 y) 5 (0-30-30 y) 9.8 y = 49[30-30- y 2 2 = 30 = 30[30y - y 2 = 490 = 49(900 - 450) = 49* = 30 050 J. 总数= 588 + 22 050 = 20 050 J. 总数= 588 + 22 050 = 0. 050 J. 总数= 20 050 = 20 050 J. 请让我重新考虑。 事实上: 当光束在高度,我们已经提升了电缆的长度(49-308 y) = 588 000; 挂线的重量为 5 450 * = = 22 050",
  "A bungee cord (which behaves like a spring with k = 50 N/m) has a natural length of 20 m. A jumper stretches it to 35 m. How much elastic potential energy is stored in the cord?": "a 跳跃器将脉冲线伸展至35米。 脉冲线中储存了多少弹性潜在能量?",
  "11,250 J": "11,250 J 11,250 J",
  "3750 J": "3750 J",
  "7500 J": "7500 J",
  "5625 J": "5625 J",
  "The stretch beyond natural length is 35 - 20 = 15 m. Elastic PE = (1/2)kx^2 = (1/2)(50)(15)^2 = 25(225) = 5625 J.": "超过自然长度的伸展度为35-20 = 15米。 Elastic PE = (1/2)kx2 = (1/2)(50)(15)2 = 25(225) = 5625 J。",
  "A factory conveyor belt moves packages using a force F(x) = 20*e^(-x/5) N. How much work is done moving a package from x = 0 to x = 10 m?": "使用F(x) = 20*e(x/5)/(N)的F(x) = 20*e(x/5)的工厂传送带移动包件。 将包件从x = 0 = x = 10米移动到x = 10米完成多少工作?",
  "20(1 - e^(-2)) J": "20(1 - e(-2)) J",
  "100*e^(-2) J": "100**(-2) J",
  "100(1 - e^(-2)) J": "100(1 - e(-2)) J",
  "200(1 - e^(-2)) J": "200(1 - e(-2)) J",
  "W = integral from 0 to 10 of 20*e^(-x/5) dx = 20[-5*e^(-x/5)] from 0 to 10 = -100[e^(-2) - e^0] = -100(e^(-2) - 1) = 100(1 - e^(-2)) J.": "W = 20 * * (-x/5) dx = 20 [-5 * e% (-x/5)] 0 = 10 = - 100 [e% (-2) - e%0] = - 100 (e% (-2) - 1) = 100(1 - e% (2) J。",
  "A 500-kg wrecking ball swings down from a height of 4 m. Using conservation of energy (g = 9.8 m/s^2), what is its speed at the bottom of the swing?": "利用节能(g = 9.8 m/s2),在秋千底部的速度如何?",
  "Approximately 6.26 m/s": "约6.26米/秒",
  "Approximately 12.52 m/s": "约12.52米/秒",
  "Approximately 8.85 m/s": "约8.85米/秒",
  "Approximately 4.43 m/s": "约4.43米/秒",
  "By conservation of energy, mgh = (1/2)mv^2, so v = sqrt(2gh) = sqrt(2*9.8*4) = sqrt(78.4) = 8.85 m/s (approximately). Mass cancels, so the speed is independent of the mass of the wrecking ball.": "通过节能, mgh = (1/2)mv2, 因此 v = sqrt( 2gh) = sqrt(2*9.8*4) = sqrt( 78.4) = 8.85 m/s( 约) 。 质量取消, 因此速度与残骸球的质量无关 。",
  "A car engine exerts a force F(x) = 3000 - 5x N as the car travels from x = 0 to x = 200 m. How much work does the engine do?": "F(x) = 3000 - 5xN 汽车在从x = 0到x = 200米之间行驶时,汽车发动机产生F(x) = 3000 - 5xN的功率。 发动机做了多少工作?",
  "600,000 J": "600 000 J",
  "300,000 J": "300,300,000 J",
  "500,000 J": "500,500,500,500,000 J",
  "400,000 J": "400 000 J",
  "W = integral from 0 to 200 of (3000 - 5x) dx = [3000x - (5/2)x^2] from 0 to 200 = 600,000 - 100,000 = 500,000 J.": "W=0至200(300 - 5x) dx=[3000x - (5/2)xx2],0至200=600,000 - 100,000=500,000焦耳。",
  "A dam holds back water 15 m deep. A pump removes water from the bottom of the reservoir through a pipe that goes over the top of the dam. If a thin layer of water at depth y (measured from the surface) has weight w(y) dy, the work to pump this layer over the dam is:": "水泵将水从水库底部通过管道从水库顶部取水。如果深水层的薄水层y(从地表测量)有重量(y)(y),在水库上抽水的工作是:",
  "w(y) * y * dy": "(y) y * y * dy (y) * y * y y y dy",
